Gauteng could go back to Alert Level 4 and 5 of the lockdown. That's because Gauteng Premier David Makhura says the province will ask the National Command Council to reinstate stricter restrictions. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Premier David Makhura says the province could go back to Alert Level 4 and 5 of the lockdown. Makhura says the province will ask the National Coronavirus Command Council to reinstate stricter restrictions. But the premier is adamant that will not happen without inclusive consultation. READ: COVID-19 rampant in Gauteng "We want to make ensure when we make this intervention that it takes into account all the various needs of our people," Makhura said. Makhura and his team gave details on the province's readiness as it gears up for the coronavirus infections peak. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.